                                <p class="title-subsection">Simplicity of UX</p>
                            </div>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">The above goal can be achieved through the implementation of digital technology for example through a digital web or mobile app that designed to increase consumer engagement to the companies and products. When talking about the effectiveness of digital products to achieve the above objectives, the most important thing to consider is how to ensure amazing user experience for consumers. Another thing that is also important to understand is the importance of developing digital products that are efficient and easy to use. The appearance of design needs to be stand out, it is not enough to just be good, it is needed to be different.</p>
                            <h1 class="sub-title">User Experience (UX)</h1>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">User experience (UX) is the process of increasing the satisfaction of users of certain sites or applications through the usability and pleasure provided in the interaction between users and products. Great user experience means your digital product is easy and intuitive. It also needs to be fun, unique, and inviting. UX includes all elements of the website and making sure the website is well structured, and users can easily move from one page to another.</p>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">When your customers use your product, you want them to have the best experience so they continue to use it and recommend your product to others. In addition, from a marketing perspective, good UX directs users to interact with you and provides feedback on how to improve your product. This is important information that you can only get from your users.</p>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">With a better UX design, your company will get the opportunity to perform better financially, be able to get higher income because of better retention, less price-sensitive, and positive word of mouth.</p>
                            <h1 class="sub-title">User Interface (UI)</h1>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">User Interface (UI) is an interface design of software, websites or applications that focuses on individual screens, pages, subpages, buttons and other visual elements that help users to communicate with devices or applications.</p>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">The goal is to make the site look more pleasing to the eye comfortable for long usage. UI can creates an emotional bond with users through attractive and beautiful designs. Normally, the UI will be implemented or done after UX has finished determining the layout design, logo, color, and typography to enhance a site. </p>
                            <p class="paragraph-content">A lot of people judge a book by its cover, it is also related to the appearance of sites. It is very important to develop good UI with consistent screen to screen, includes the graphics and animations, layout, and ease of use.  UI also not only focus on aesthetics but also maximizes the responsiveness, efficiency, and accessibility of websites. In other words, UI design will help increase conversion rates on a website. Companies need to develop a good user interface, it is very important because it can attract more consumers by facilitates good interaction between users and your website or mobile application.</p>
